## Completed Work This Session

### Project: arkiv — All 5 phases (Tasks #824-828)
TypeScript drop-in replacement for archiver (17.7M weekly downloads, inactive maintenance). Zero runtime dependencies, Node.js 18+, ESM+CJS dual build.

Core: CRC32 table-based (IEEE polynomial, incremental). ZIP writer: streaming with DEFLATE/STORE, data descriptors, central directory, ZIP64 extensions, UTF-8 flag, archive comments, configurable zlib levels. TAR writer: ustar headers, 512-byte block alignment, PAX extended headers for paths >255 chars and files >8GB, prefix/name splitting, gzip wrapper. Archiver engine extending Transform: append(stream/Buffer/string), file(path), directory(recursive), glob(pattern with **, *, ?, braces), symlink. Entry queue, finalize() Promise, abort(), pointer(), progress events. Built-in GlobWalker. Compat layer: archiver() factory, archiver.create(), isRegisteredFormat().

104 tests across 7 test files. Strict TypeScript. CI green on Node 18/20/22. MIT license.

